(88, 119, 'Mike stern photo.jpg', 'Mike Stern', 'The Script Reader', '<p><span>15 plus&nbsp;years as a story&nbsp;analyst. &nbsp;Current consultant for Resolution (Agency). Former story analyst for William Morris Agency. Graduate of University of Michigan Film Program.</span></p>', 'Los Angeles', 0, '', '<p>Mike Stern attended the University of Michigan in Ann Arbor, where he earned a BA in Film Studies with an emphasis in Screenwriting. He was the first winner of United Talent Agency''s College Screenwriting Competition as well as the recipient of the Hopwood Literary Award, Alice Webber Glover Playwriting Grant and a Trueblood Fellow.</p>\r\n<p>He moved to Los Angeles and began his development career at Sony Pictures and Signature Entertainment reading scripts and writing coverage for such films as&nbsp;<em>Blade, The Opposite of Sex</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Slums of Beverly Hills</em>. In 2000 Mike sold his film&nbsp;<em>Final Cut,&nbsp;</em>which he wrote and directed, to Lorne Michaels'' Broadway Video.</p>\r\n<p>In 2002, Mike segued to William Morris Agency where he worked as a full time Story Analyst providing coverage and analysis for such films as&nbsp;<em>Monster</em>&nbsp;with Charlize Theron,&nbsp;<em>Something''s Gotta Give</em>with Jack Nicholson and Keanu Reeves,&nbsp;<em>Elf</em>&nbsp;with Will Farrell, and&nbsp;<em>The Interpreter</em>&nbsp;with Sean Penn and Nicole Kidman. During his WMA tenure, his short film&nbsp;<em>Study Break</em>&nbsp;was broadcast on AMC''s MonsterFest.</p>\r\n<p>Mike has worked as a Story Analyst for Resolution and independently offered script analysis and story development through The Script Reader since 2007. Some of his successful clients include Emmy winners and show-runners. He has been the judge of screenwriting competitions and given analysis on scripts that have made it through the Hollywood maze and been successfully produced. His film&nbsp;<em>Pop the Question</em>&nbsp;was screened at the 2009 San Diego Film Festival and the 2010 Palm Springs International Film Festival. He''s currently developing a television series with Orchid Lane Productions and is writing and producing a feature film that will begin principal photography in 2015. Mr. Stern is also an actor and has worked as a professional stand-in for Tom Cruise. He can be seen in&nbsp;<em>Jack Reacher</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Edge of Tomorrow</em>.</p>', 'a:8:{i:0;s:15:"Script Coverage";i:1;s:17:"Script Consultant";i:2;s:17:"Development Notes";i:3;s:14:"Script Writing";i:4;s:13:"Ghost Writing";i:5;s:18:"Rewrite Assistance";i:6;s:32:"Proofreading & Script Formatting";i:7;s:18:"Phone Consultation";}', 'a:3:{i:0;s:17:"Script Consultant";i:1;s:13:"Script Reader";i:2;s:13:"Script Writer";}', 'http://thescriptreader.com', '', '', '', NULL, '', 'William Morris, Resolution, Sony', 'German', '', '', 'Coverage Sample - Pamela Jaye Smith.pdf', '', '', 0, '2015-07-14 20:56:47', '2015-07-14 17:58:44'),
(89, 120, 'linda_color_3.jpg', 'Linda Cowgill', 'Plots Inc. Productions', '<div class="resume_content">\r\n<p><span>Linda Cowgill heads screenwriting at The Los Angeles Film School. &nbsp;She&nbsp;</span>began her screenwriting career after completing her MFA at UCLA''s School of Film and Television. &nbsp;She covered screenplays for various production companies and talent agencies. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'Los Angeles', 0, '', '<p class="p_normal">Linda Cowgill began her screenwriting career after completing her MFA at UCLA''s School of Film and Television. While covering scripts for various agencies and production houses, she landed her first job writing for&nbsp;<em>THE INCREDIBLE HULK</em>&nbsp;at Universal Television.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="p_normal">She sold a feature screenplay that Orion Pictures produced. The film,&nbsp;<em>OPPOSING FORCE</em>, starred Tom Skerrit, Lisa Eichhorn, Anthony Zerbe and Richard Roundtree, but was credited to Gil Cowan -- Linda''s pseudonym after seeing a rough cut of the film.</p>\r\n<p class="p_normal">Linda has written television and films for Paramount, Universal, MGM, Warner Bros., and several small independents. She wrote for the acclaimed series&nbsp;<em>LIFE GOES ON</em>&nbsp;before her daughter arrived on the scene. Since then, she has focused more on teaching screenwriting.</p>\r\n<p class="p_normal">She has taught seminars and workshops at the American Film Institute, the Kennedy Center in Washington, D.C., the Boston Film Institute, Loyola Marymount University, IFP Miami and NALIP. She currently heads the Screenwriting Department at the Los Angeles Film School. Her books,&nbsp;<em>Secrets of Screenplay Structure</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Writing Short Films,</em>&nbsp;are used at colleges and universities across the US, Canada and the UK. Recently,&nbsp;<em>Writing Short Films</em>&nbsp;has been translated into German, and&nbsp;<em>Secrets of Screenplay Structure</em>&nbsp;into Korean.</p>\r\n<p class="p_normal">Her experience mentoring screenwriters in the LA Film School''s Feature Film Development Program led her to create&nbsp;<strong>The&nbsp;Art&nbsp;of&nbsp;Plotting</strong>&nbsp;seminar. Linda saw that while her writers were using structural concepts, they were still not maximizing the emotional, creative and technical potential of their stories. Building on the lessons she gave to those writers,&nbsp;<strong>The Art of Plotting</strong>hopes to provide other writers with the effective tools to weave the threads of their stories into emotional, compelling and unified wholes.</p>', 'a:8:{i:0;s:15:"Script Coverage";i:1;s:17:"Script Consultant";i:2;s:17:"Development Notes";i:3;s:14:"Script Writing";i:4;s:13:"Ghost Writing";i:5;s:18:"Rewrite Assistance";i:6;s:32:"Proofreading & Script Formatting";i:7;s:18:"Phone Consultation";}', 'a:1:{i:0;s:10:"WGA Member";}', 'http://www.plotsinc.com/sitenew/about.html', '', '', '', NULL, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '2016-02-26 03:27:14', '2015-07-14 21:07:53'),
(90, 129, 'Unknown.jpeg', 'Sonia Bhalla', '', '<p>Sonia got her start as an assistant director working on such films as the&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SIXTH SENSE and UP IN THE AIR. &nbsp;She wrote and will be direct her first feature film, Modern Love which is currently in pre-production.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 0, '', '<p>As a member of the Director''s Guild, Sonia worked her way up through the Guild ranks choosing her projects carefully. Her talents, personality, and leadership skills earned her the highly demanding and coveted team position of Assistant director alongside Academy Award winning and nominated Directors; Ron Howard, M. Night Shyamalan, Paul Thomas Anderson, and Jason Reitman. &nbsp;The DGA has nominated &nbsp;Sonia twice for her work on "The Sixth Sense" and "Up in the Air," starring George Clooney. &nbsp;She has also worked on numerous hit television comedies including "Outsource" where she served as Producer and director.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:1:{i:0;s:14:"Script Writing";}', 'a:3:{i:0;s:13:"Script Writer";i:1;s:8:"Director";i:2;s:8:"Producer";}', '', '', '', '', NULL, 'BA in Political Science, Syracuse University', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'ABC/DISNEY Television Director''s program (2012-2014)', 0, '2015-07-29 18:21:59', '2015-07-24 20:16:14'),
